<subSubSection id="C37398FDFF95FF97FF6381FDB66EF990" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD6CB76FF95FF97FF6381FDB6C5FAB0" blockId="12.[151,1437,988,1879]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FF6381FDB679FB68" bold="true" box="[199,519,1204,1230]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
Neotropical species released throughout the African cassava belt in the 80’s for the control of the cassava green mite 
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF95FF97FD9D8191B7D3FB55" authority="(Bondar)" baseAuthorityName="Bondar" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[569,941,1240,1267]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetranychidae" genus="Mononychellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanajoa">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FD9D8191B73FFB54" box="[569,833,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Mononychellus tanajoa</emphasis>
(Bondar)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FC1F8191B0E4FB54" author="Yaninek, J. S. &amp; Megevand, B. &amp; de Moraes, G. &amp; Bakker, F. &amp; Braun, A. &amp; Herren, H. R." box="[955,1178,1240,1267]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="323 - 330" refId="ref17393" refString="Yaninek, J. S., Megevand, B., de Moraes, G. J, Bakker, F., Braun, A. &amp; Herren, H. R. (1992) Establishment of the neotropical predator Amblyseius idaeus (Acari: Phytoseiidae) in Benin, West Africa. BioControl Science and Technology, 1, 323 - 330. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09583159109355211" type="journal article" year="1992">
Yaninek 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FB848190B02FFB54" box="[1056,1105,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FB018191B09FFB54" author="Yaninek, J. S. &amp; Onzo, A. &amp; Ojo, B." box="[1189,1249,1240,1266]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="145 - 160" refId="ref17470" refString="Yaninek, J. S., Onzo, A. &amp; Ojo, B. (1993) Continent-wide releases of neotropical phytoseiids against the exotic cassava green mite in Africa. Experimental and Applied Acarology, 17, 145 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00156950" type="journal article" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
). Also present in 
<collectingCountry id="F37E8BE6FF95FF97FF3381B5B566FAB0" box="[151,280,1276,1302]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
islands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FED881B5B6D1FAB0" author="Ferragut, F. &amp; Baumann, J." box="[380,687,1276,1303]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="1113 - 1138" refId="ref14915" refString="Ferragut, F. &amp; Baumann, J. (2021) Hidden biodiversity in the Atlantic Islands. Amblyseiinae (Acari: Phytoseiidae) from Madeira archipelago. Systematic and Applied Acarology, 25, 1113 - 1138. https: // doi. org / 10.11158 / saa. 25.6.14" type="journal article" year="2021">Ferragut &amp; Baumann 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD6CB76FF95FF97FF638069B66EF990" blockId="12.[151,1437,988,1879]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FF638069B5ADFA9C" bold="true" box="[199,467,1312,1338]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Additional description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount id="9D6F00FFFF95FF97FE458069B60FFA9D" box="[481,625,1312,1339]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" type="female">five females</specimenCount>
). Dorsal shield 332 (320–349) long, 154 (149–161) wide. Dorsal setae 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FA228069B1E2FA9C" box="[1414,1436,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">j1</emphasis>
21 (19–24), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FEBB800DB54BFAF8" box="[287,309,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">j3</emphasis>
48 (47–50), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FE66800DB5A6FAF8" box="[450,472,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">j4</emphasis>
40 (38–42), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FDC2800DB602FAF8" box="[614,636,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">j5</emphasis>
42 (41–44), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FCAD800DB761FAF8" box="[777,799,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">j6</emphasis>
57 (55–61), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FC09800DB7B9FAF8" box="[941,967,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">J2</emphasis>
59 (53–63), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FBF1800DB011FAF8" box="[1109,1135,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">J5</emphasis>
11 (10–12), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FB58800DB16AFAF8" box="[1276,1300,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">z2</emphasis>
49 (45–53), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FF338021B4CEFA24" box="[151,176,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">z4</emphasis>
49 (46–54), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FEE78021B522FA24" box="[323,348,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">z5</emphasis>
42 (40–43), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FE4B8021B673FA24" box="[495,525,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Z1</emphasis>
57 (54–59), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FD048021B6C0FA24" box="[672,702,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Z4</emphasis>
61 (58–68), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FCF58021B710FA24" box="[849,878,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Z5</emphasis>
66 (60–73), 
<geoCoordinate id="EE5DADB1FF95FF97FBA58021B040FA25" box="[1025,1086,1384,1411]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="58" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" precision="925" value="-4.9666667">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FBA58021B064FA24" box="[1025,1050,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">s4</emphasis>
58
</geoCoordinate>
(53–64), 
<geoCoordinate id="EE5DADB1FF95FF97FB098021B093FA25" box="[1197,1261,1384,1411]" degrees="2" direction="south" minutes="58" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" precision="925" value="-2.9666667">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FB098021B0B7FA24" box="[1197,1225,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">S2</emphasis>
58
</geoCoordinate>
(50–63), 
<geoCoordinate id="EE5DADB1FF95FF97FAF88021B1E2FA24" box="[1372,1436,1384,1410]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="42" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" precision="925" value="-4.7">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FAF88021B107FA24" box="[1372,1401,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">S4</emphasis>
42
</geoCoordinate>
(36–46), 
<geoCoordinate id="EE5DADB1FF95FF97FEA480C5B53FFA00" box="[256,321,1420,1446]" degrees="5" direction="south" minutes="42" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" precision="925" value="-5.7">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FEA480C5B562FA00" box="[256,284,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">S5</emphasis>
42
</geoCoordinate>
(31–48). Sublaterals 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FD9C80C5B62FFA00" box="[568,593,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">r3</emphasis>
42 (33–47), 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FD4C80C5B779FA00" box="[744,775,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">R1</emphasis>
39 (35–42). Length of peritremes 170 (168–173). Sternal shield wider than long; 57 (55–60) long, 66 (65–68) wide. Ventrianal shield 110 (106–119) long, 81 (76–90) wide at level of setae 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FEEB809DB500FA48" box="[335,382,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">ZV2</emphasis>
, 72 (68–80) wide at level of anus. Distance between pre-anal pores 18 (16–21). Setae 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FAE9809DB107FA48" box="[1357,1401,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">JV5</emphasis>
51 (48–53). Genua II and III with seven setae. Setal formula of genu II 2 2/0, 2/0 1; of genu III 1 2/1, 2/0 1. Macroseta on basitarsus IV 56 (49–62) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37398FDFF95FF97FF638309B003F8F0" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD6CB76FF95FF97FF638309B003F8F0" blockId="12.[151,1437,988,1879]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FF638309B54AF9FC" bold="true" box="[199,308,1600,1626]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Remarks</emphasis>
. It has been demonstrated the morphological variability of this species (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FB618309B1E9F9FC" author="Tixier, M. - S. &amp; Tsolakis, H. &amp; Ragusa, S. &amp; Poinso, A. &amp; Ferrero, M. &amp; Okassa, M. &amp; Kreiter, S." box="[1221,1431,1600,1627]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="273 - 281" refId="ref16905" refString="Tixier, M. - S., Tsolakis, H., Ragusa, S., Poinso, A., Ferrero, M., Okassa, M. &amp; Kreiter, S. (2011) Integrative taxonomy demonstrates the unexpected synonymy between two predatory mite species: Cydnodromus idaeus and C. picanus (Acari: Phytoseiidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 273 - 281. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 11025" type="journal article" year="2011">
Tixier 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FAB18308B135F9FC" box="[1301,1355,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FF33832CB5B0F9D8" author="Ferragut, F. &amp; Baumann, J." box="[151,462,1636,1663]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="1113 - 1138" refId="ref14915" refString="Ferragut, F. &amp; Baumann, J. (2021) Hidden biodiversity in the Atlantic Islands. Amblyseiinae (Acari: Phytoseiidae) from Madeira archipelago. Systematic and Applied Acarology, 25, 1113 - 1138. https: // doi. org / 10.11158 / saa. 25.6.14" type="journal article" year="2021">Ferragut &amp; Baumann 2021</bibRefCitation>
), in particular with reference to the position of setae 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FB8A832DB031F9D8" box="[1070,1103,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">st3</emphasis>
and the occurrence of dorsal solenostome 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FE8E83C1B52AF904" box="[298,340,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">gd2</emphasis>
. All the females examined have the setae 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FC8283C1B739F904" box="[806,839,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">st3</emphasis>
inserted on the posterior part of the sternal shield and the gland opening 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FEC283E5B5EEF960" box="[358,400,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">gd2</emphasis>
is absent (they only have 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FD1683E5B6A2F960" box="[690,732,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">gd1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FD4D83E5B76DF960" box="[745,787,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">gd6</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FCED83E5B70DF960" box="[841,883,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">gd9</emphasis>
). In general, the setal measurements were similar to those reported for specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F37E8BE6FF95FF97FD9F8399B6D4F94C" box="[571,682,1744,1770]" name="Argentina" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F37E8BE6FF95FF97FD458399B760F94C" box="[737,798,1744,1770]" name="Chile" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FC888399B069F94C" author="Guanilo, A. D. &amp; de Moraes, G. &amp; Toledo, S. &amp; Knapp, M." box="[812,1047,1744,1771]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref15179" refString="Guanilo, A. D., de Moraes, G. J, Toledo, S. &amp; Knapp, M. (2008 a) Phytoseiid mites (Acari: Phytoseiidae) from Argentina, with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 1884 (1), 1 - 35. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1884.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Guanilo 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FC2B8398B7BFF94C" box="[911,961,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">et al</emphasis>
. 2008a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FB868398B0CAF94C" author="Ragusa, S." box="[1058,1204,1744,1771]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="3 - 10" refId="ref16250" refString="Ragusa, S. (2000) A new Cydnodromus (Parasitiformes, Phytoseiidae), from the desert of northern Chile. Phytophaga, 10, 3 - 10." type="journal article" year="2000">
Ragusa 
<quantity id="4C916693FF95FF97FBD88399B0CAF94C" box="[1148,1204,1744,1770]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" unit="in" value="2000.0">2000</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
in the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C69B0F5FF95FF97FF3383BDB50EF8A8" baseAuthorityName="Ragusa" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[151,368,1780,1806]" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" genus="Neoseiulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picanus">
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FF3383BDB50EF8A8" box="[151,368,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Neoseiulus picanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F37E8BE6FF95FF97FE2C83BDB5B2F8A8" box="[392,460,1780,1806]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FE7883BDB775F8A8" author="Moraes, G. J. de &amp; McMurtry, J. A." box="[476,779,1780,1807]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="131 - 148" refId="ref15944" refString="Moraes, G. J. de &amp; McMurtry, J. A. (1983) Phytoseiid mites (Acarina) of Northeastern Brazil with descriptions of four new species. International Journal of Acarology, 9, 131 - 148. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647958308683326" type="journal article" year="1983">Moraes &amp; McMurtry 1983</bibRefCitation>
) and other South American countries. On the contrary, the females were a 10% smaller and the dorsal setae about a 10% shorter than those reported for mites collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F37E8BE6FF95FF97FAC78251B4A6F8F0" name="Cape Verde" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF8B687FF95FF97FF438275B664F8F0" author="Ferragut, F. &amp; Baumann, J." box="[231,538,1852,1879]" pageId="12" pageNumber="535" pagination="1113 - 1138" refId="ref14915" refString="Ferragut, F. &amp; Baumann, J. (2021) Hidden biodiversity in the Atlantic Islands. Amblyseiinae (Acari: Phytoseiidae) from Madeira archipelago. Systematic and Applied Acarology, 25, 1113 - 1138. https: // doi. org / 10.11158 / saa. 25.6.14" type="journal article" year="2021">Ferragut &amp; Baumann 2021</bibRefCitation>
), which moreover have pores 
<emphasis id="B91D1764FF95FF97FCCE8275B7EAF8F0" box="[874,916,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="535">gd2</emphasis>
on the dorsal shield.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
